Tue May 12 07:55:19 GMT 2009  Richard Boulton <richard@lemurconsulting.com>

	* flax/searchserver/application.py,flax/searchserver/queries.py:
	  Add a set of classes to define Queries and Searches; the idea is
	  that application.py will parse the search parameters into these
	  classes, such that the backends simply have to take a Search
	  object and convert it into the appropriate search (or raise an
	  exception if that's not possible).  All the validation will live
	  in application.py (or, at least, not in backends).  Also, some
	  tidyups to validation and to documentation comments.

